            <div class="post-title">
                <h3>Publications</h3>
                
            </div>

            <h4 id="2026">2026</h4>
<p><strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, S. Cornell. <em>Exploiting Noise Inseparability for Weakly-Supervised Discriminative Speech Denoising Using Noisy Targets</em>. Under Review</p>
<p><strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, S. Cornell. <em>Ring Mixing with Auxiliary Signal-to-Consistency-Error Ratio Loss for Unsupervised Denoising in Speech Separation</em>. Under Review [<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.08415">arXiv</a>]</p>
<p>D. Klement, <strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, S. Khudanpur, J. Černocký, L. Burget. <em>Unsupervised Speech Enhancement using Data-defined Priors</em>. Under Review [<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2509.22942">arXiv</a>]</p>
<p><strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>. <em>Single-Microphone Audio Point Source Discriminative Localization from Reverberation Late Tail Estimation</em>. ICASSP. 2026 [<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.09627">arXiv</a>]</p>
<p>X. He, A. Polok, J. Villalba, T. Thebaud, <strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>. <em>Scaling Multi-Talker ASR with Speaker-Agnostic Activity Streams</em>. ICASSP. 2026 [<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2510.03630">arXiv</a>]</p>
<p>Z. Huang, <strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, L.P. Garcia Perera, S. Watanabe, S. Khudanpur. <em>CSPB: Conversational Speech Processing Benchmark for Self-supervised Speech Models</em>. EACL. 2026 [<a href="https://aclanthology.org/2026.eacl-long.275/">ACL</a>]</p>
<h4 id="2025">2025</h4>
<p><strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>. <em>Speaker Conditioning of Voice Activity Detection via Implicit Separation</em>. Interspeech. 2025 [<a href="https://www.isca-archive.org/interspeech_2025/maciejewski25_interspeech.html">ISCA</a>]</p>
<p>D. Palzer, <strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, E. Fosler-Lussier. <em>End-to-End Diarization utilizing Attractor Deep Clustering</em>. Interspeech. 2025 [<a href="https://www.isca-archive.org/interspeech_2025/palzer25_interspeech.html">ISCA</a>]</p>
<h4 id="2024">2024</h4>
<p>A. Polok, D. Klement, J. Han, Š. Sedláček, B. Yusuf, <strong>Matthew Maciejewski</strong>, M. Wiesner, L. Burget. <em>BUT/JHU System Description for CHiME-8 NOTSOFAR-1 Challenge</em> CHiME. 2024 [<a href="https://www.isca-archive.org/chime_2024/polok24_chime.html">ISCA</a>]</p>
<p>S. Cornell, T.J. Park, H. Huang, C. Boeddeker, X. Chang, <strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, M. Wiesner, P. Garcia, S. Watanabe. <em>The CHiME-8 DASR Challenge for Generalizable and Array Agnostic Distant Automatic Speech Recognition and Diarization</em>. CHiME. 2024 [<a href="https://www.isca-archive.org/chime_2024/cornell24_chime.html">ISCA</a>]</p>
<p><strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, D. Klement, R. Huang, M. Wisner, S. Khudanpur. <em>Evaluating the Santa Barbara Corpus: Challenges of the Breadth of Conversational Spoken Language</em>. Interspeech. 2024 [<a href="https://www.isca-speech.org/archive/interspeech_2024/maciejewski24_interspeech.html">ISCA</a>]</p>
<p>D. Raj, M. Wiesner, <strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, L.P. Garcia-Perera, D. Povey, S. Khudanpur. <em>On Speaker Attribution with SURT</em>. Odyssey. 2024 [<a href="https://www.isca-archive.org/odyssey_2024/raj24_odyssey.html">ISCA</a>]</p>
<p>D. Palzer, <strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, E. Fosler-Lussier. <em>Improving Neural Diarization Through Speaker Attribute Attractors and Local Dependency Modeling</em>. IEEE ICASSP. 2024 [<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2506.05593">arXiv</a>]</p>
<h4 id="2023">2023</h4>
<p>S. Cornell, M. Wiesner, S. Watanabe, D. Raj, X. Chang, P. Garcia, <strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, Y. Masuyama, Z.-Q. Wang, S. Squartini, S. Khudanpur. <em>The CHiME-7 DASR Challenge: Distant Meeting Transcription with Multiple Devices in Diverse Scenarios</em>. Proc. CHiME-7. 2023 [<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2306.13734">arXiv</a>]</p>
<p><strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, J. Shi, S. Watanabe, S. Khudanpur. <em>A Dilemma of Ground Truth in Noisy Speech Separation and an Approach to Lessen the Impact of Imperfect Training Data</em>. Computer Speech &amp; Language. 2023</p>
<h4 id="2021">2021</h4>
<p><strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, <em>Towards Single-Channel Speech Separation in Noise and Reverberation</em>. PhD Dissertation, Johns Hopkins University. 2021 [<a href="https://www.mmaciejewski.com/dissertation.pdf">pdf</a>]</p>
<p><strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, S. Watanabe, S. Khudanpur. <em>Speaker Verification-Based Evaluation of Single-Channel Speech Separation</em>. Interspeech. 2021 [<a href="https://www.isca-speech.org/archive/interspeech_2021/maciejewski21_interspeech.html">ISCA</a>]</p>
<p><strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, J. Shi, S. Watanabe, S. Khudanpur. <em>Training Noisy Single-Channel Speech Separation With Noisy Oracle Sources: A Large Gap and A Small Step</em>. IEEE ICASSP. 2021 [<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2010.12430">arXiv</a>]</p>
<h4 id="2020">2020</h4>
<p><strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, G. Wichern, E. McQuinn, J. Le Roux. <em>WHAMR!: Noisy and Reverberant Single-Channel Speech Separation</em>. IEEE ICASSP. 2020 [<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1910.10279">arXiv</a>]</p>
<p>A. Arora, D. Raj, A.S. Subramanian, K. Li, B. Ben-Yair, <strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, P. Żelasko, P. Garcia, S. Watanabe, S. Khudanpur. <em>The JHU Multi-Microphone Multi-Speaker ASR System for the CHiME-6 Challenge</em>. Proc. CHiME-6. 2020 [<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2006.07898">arXiv</a>]</p>
<h4 id="2019">2019</h4>
<p><strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, G. Sell, Y. Fujita, L.P. Garcia-Perera, S. Watanabe, and S. Khudanpur. <em>Analysis of Robustness of Deep Single-Channel Speech Separation Using Corpora Constructed From Multiple Domains</em>. IEEE WASPAA. 2019</p>
<h4 id="2018">2018</h4>
<p>N. Kanda, R. Ikeshita, S. Horiguchi, Y. Fujita, K. Nagamatsu, X. Wang, V. Manohar, N.E.Y. Soplin, <strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, S.J. Chen, A.S. Subramanian, R. Li, Z. Wang, J. Naradowsky, L.P. Garcia-Perera, G. Sell. <em>The Hitachi/JHU CHiME-5 system: Advances in speech recognition for everyday home environments using multiple microphone arrays</em>. Proc. CHiME-5. 2018 [<a href="https://www.isca-speech.org/archive/chime_2018/kanda18_chime.html">ISCA</a>]</p>
<p>G. Sell, D. Snyder, A. McCree, D. Garcia-Romero, J. Villalba, <strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, V. Manohar, N. Dehak, D. Povey, S. Watanabe, and S. Khudanpur. <em>Diarization is Hard: Some Experiences and Lessons Learned for the JHU Team in the Inaugural DIHARD Challenge</em>. Interspeech. 2018 [<a href="https://www.isca-speech.org/archive/interspeech_2018/sell18_interspeech.html">ISCA</a>]</p>
<p><strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, D. Snyder, V. Manohar, N. Dehak, and S. Khudanpur. <em>Characterizing Performance of Speaker Diarization Systems on Far-field Speech using Standard Methods</em>. IEEE ICASSP. 2018</p>
<p>N. Ryant, E. Bergelson, K. Church, A. Cristia, J. Du, S. Ganapathy, S. Khudanpur, D. Kowalski, M. Krishnamoorthy, R. Kulshreshta, M. Liberman, Y.D. Lu, <strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, F. Metze, J. Profant, L. Sun, Y. Tsaok, Z. Yum. <em>Enhancement and Analysis of Conversational Speech: JSALT 2017</em>. IEEE ICASSP. 2018</p>
<h4 id="2016">2016</h4>
<p>E. Chodroff, <strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, J. Trmal, S. Khudanpur, J. Godfrey. <em>New release of Mixer-6: Improved validity for phonetic study of speaker variation and identification</em>. LREC. 2016</p>
<h4 id="2015">2015</h4>
<p>H. Hermansky, L. Burget, J. Cohen, E. Dupoux, N. Feldman, J. Godfrey, S. Khudanpur, <strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, S.H. Mallidi, A. Menon, T. Ogawa, V. Peddinti, R. Rose, R. Stern, M. Wiesner, K. Veselý. <em>Towards machines that know when they do not know: Summary of work done at 2014 Frederick Jelinek Memorial Workshop</em>. IEEE ICASSP. 2015</p>
<p>H.M. Park, <strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, C. Kim, R. Stern. <em>Robust automatic speech recognition in reverberation: onset enhancement versus binaural source separation</em>. The Journal of the Acoustical Society of America. 2015</p>
<h4 id="2014">2014</h4>
<p>H.M. Park, <strong>M. Maciejewski</strong>, C. Kim, R. Stern. <em>Robust speech recognition in reverberant environments using subband-based steady-state monaural and binaural suppression</em>. Interspeech. 2014 [<a href="https://www.isca-speech.org/archive/interspeech_2014/park14_interspeech.html">ISCA</a>]</p>
